  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nAfter numerous attempts to sync geth and parity \"fast\" nodes on my system with no success a whisper of hope was offered to me when a geth \"light\" node just magically synced within minutes. Unfortunately the hope didn't last long as it appears that \"light\" mode doesn't have any way to receive pending transactions. Am I wrong? If not - are there any plans to include this feature or is this technically infeasible? :)\r\n\r\nWhats I've tried: used RPC methods: \"eth_newPendingTransactionFilter\" in conjunction with \"eth_getFilterChanges\" and there were no filter changes ever reported. \"txpool_content\" also seems to be empty all the time. I will provide code examples if this feature is in fact somewhat supported.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.1.  Same on nightly\r\nOS & Version: Mac OS X\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nget some pending transctions\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nno pending transactions to be seen",
