    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A light client only maintains its own transactions. It cannot maintain a pool of pending transactions, since it cannot check the validity of those transactions (without the state, which is costly to pull from the network for every single tx).\r\n\r\nI don't think this is a use case we will ever be able to support. Accessing any \"pending\" data with a light client is already problematic because the result would depend on which server is answering you (since nodes in the network may see different pending states).\r\n\r\nSorry to say, but I don't think light client will help you here.",
